Description:
My Dublin based client that is in the Utility Industry is looking for a Lead DevOps Engineer to join their team. 




Job Responsibilities

Working with data scientists on refining their algorithms for production deployment, performance, model accuracy and artifact management, along with automating & streamlining parts of this process;
Owning and developing the deployment strategy for data processing and machine learning platforms using infrastructure practices as code on Microsoft Azure;
Ensure that the infrastructure and code is delivered incrementally and according to the internal security deployment policies;
Author high-quality, high-performance, unit-tested code to extract and transform data based on business and data science needs;
Ensure pipelines are deployable and sustainable at scale and meets the business needs;
Mentoring and building out a small team of DevOps and MLOps engineers;
Working directly with stakeholders, engineering, and test to create high quality solutions that solve end-user problems;
Developing and executing agile work plans for iterative and incremental project delivery; and
Demonstrate exceptional impact in delivery of projects, products and/or platforms in terms of scalable data processing and application architectures, technical deliverables and delivery throughout the project lifecycle.




Experience Required

Experience in the managing of deployment to cloud systems (preferably Microsoft Azure) through Infrastructure As Code solution (preferably Terraform);
Knowledge of cloud based networking, access management and security, log analysis etc;
Bachelor degree (Masters advantageous) in computer science or equivalent software engineering discipline;
Experience in the deployment and management of Kubernetes clusters, writing Docker images & image management; 
Experience researching and applying devops best practices in processes such as git branching strategies, version control and code review process;
Design and implementation of devops pipelines to validate, build, test, and deploy different content such as scale packages, docker packages and python packages;
Experience implementing automated solutions to improve code quality e.g unit testing, integration etc.;
Strong problem solving and software debugging skills;
Effectively explain technical concepts & whiteboarding; and
Experience with Agile development methodologies. 




